   From behind bars, Nelson Mandela has dominated the fight for black rights in South Africa.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The following are some of the key events in his life. Mandela joins the African National Congress at age 26, later becoming president of the group's Youth League.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   When the National Party comes to power in 1948, the ANC begins planning a campaign of civil disobedience to fight the party's apartheid policy . President Pieter W. Botha offers to free Mandela if he renounces violence; Mandela refuses until the government takes steps to dismantle apartheid and grants full political rights to blacks .
  </a>
